Usage:
  config-connector powertools change-state-into-spec [flags]

Flags:
      --as string            Username to impersonate for the operation. User could be a regular user or a service account in a namespace.
      --as-group strings     Group to impersonate for the operation, this flag can be repeated to specify multiple groups.
      --dry-run              dry-run mode will not make changes, but only print the changes it would make
  -h, --help                 help for change-state-into-spec
      --keep-field strings   Additional fields to preserve in the spec, even if they were set by state-into-spec=merge (example .spec.location)
      --kind string          Kind of the object to change
      --kubeconfig string    Path to the kubeconfig file to use for CLI requests.
      --name string          Name of the object to change
  -n, --namespace string     Namespace of the object
      --set string           New value for the state-into-spec annotation (default "absent")

Global Flags:
  -v, --verbose   enable verbose logging (disabled by default)

